verbose_text: Radiologic features of eGBM include areas of cystic necrosis with nodular enhancement, often accompanied by vasogenic edema and associated mass effect.4 Tumor location and morphology can assist in differentiating primary brain tumors from solitary intracerebral metastases with contrast enhanced MRI.
